{
  "texts": [
    "The work [234] proposed to evaluate FedFM by comparing the performance of the federated parameterefficient fine-tuned model with traditional centralized finetuning methods.",
    "FedIT [235] leverages FL framework for FM instruction tuning and conducted studies on the widely used GPT-4 to exploit the heterogeneous and diverse sets of instructions.",
    "FedNLP [236] is a benchmark framework for evaluating FL methods on four common formulations of NLP tasks: text classification, sequence tagging, question answering and seq2seq generation.",
    "They proposed a universal interface between Transformer-based language models (e.g., BERT, BART) and FL methods under various non-IID partitioning strategies.",
    "SV-based methods have been extensively employed in conventional FL scenarios to assess the contribution of each participant."
  ]
}